## 4. Structural Diagrams & Schematics

### 4.1 Form Validation Workflow — Block-Level Functional Architecture

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A[User Opens Form Page] --> B[User Fills Input Fields]
    B --> C{User Clicks Submit Button}
    C --> D[onsubmit Event Fires]
    D --> E[JavaScript validateForm Function Executes]
    E --> F[Read All Input Values via DOM]
    F --> G[Apply Validation Rules Sequentially]
    G --> H{All Rules Pass?}
    H -- No --> I[Display Error Messages in span Elements]
    I --> J[Call event.preventDefault to Block Submission]
    J --> K[User Corrects Errors and Resubmits]
    K --> C
    H -- Yes --> L[Allow Form Submission to Server]
    L --> M[Show Success Message]
    M --> N[End]
```

### 4.2 Validation Rule Decision Tree

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    Start[Validate Field] --> Empty{Is Field Empty?}
    Empty -- Yes --> E1[Show Required Error]
    Empty -- No --> Len{Is Length Adequate?}
    Len -- No --> E2[Show Length Error]
    Len -- Yes --> Pat{Matches Regex Pattern?}
    Pat -- No --> E3[Show Pattern Error]
    Pat -- Yes --> Range{Within Allowed Range?}
    Range -- No --> E4[Show Range Error]
    Range -- Yes --> Pass[Field is Valid]
    E1 --> Fail[Mark Form Invalid]
    E2 --> Fail
    E3 --> Fail
    E4 --> Fail
```

### 4.3 Event Binding Architecture

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    subgraph Browser
        HTML[HTML Form Element]
        DOM[Document Object Model]
        JS[JavaScript Engine]
    end

    User[User Action Click or Submit] --> HTML
    HTML -- triggers --> JS
    JS -- reads --> DOM
    JS -- updates error spans --> DOM
    DOM -- renders feedback --> User
    JS -- preventDefault on failure --> HTML
    HTML -- submits to server on success --> Server[Backend Server]
```

### 4.4 Client-Side vs Server-Side Validation — Comparative Architecture

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    subgraph Client_Browser
        UI[HTML Form] --> JSVal[JavaScript Validator]
        JSVal -->|Invalid| Stop[Block Submit and Show Errors]
        JSVal -->|Valid| Forward[Forward Data to Server]
    end

    Stop --> UI
    Forward --> ServerVal[Server Side Validator]
    ServerVal -->|Invalid| Reject[Reject Request]
    ServerVal -->|Valid| Store[Store in Database]
```

